The patch's main checkpoint/resume behavior still treats successful abstentions as missing on resume, causing repeat calls and possible result changes after relaunch. This is a correctness issue in the new resilience semantics.

Review comment:

- [P2] Preserve successful abstentions on resume — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/python/eval/m1_baseline.py:774-775
  When a checkpoint contains a legitimate successful abstention (`answers[arm] = None`), `prior_answers_from_artifact` returns that key with value `None`, but this resume path only reuses non-`None` values. Any relaunched run therefore re-calls every persisted abstention, spending again and potentially converting a previously scored abstention into a missing failure if the endpoint is down; this contradicts the new failure-vs-abstention split. The resume logic needs a way to distinguish key-present `None` abstentions from absent failed cells.
